<TITLE> Govt raises tax-free income bar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 29 (bdnews24.com)  The cabinet Sunday decided to lift the tax-free income ceiling to Tk 165,000 from Tk 150,000, a government spokesman said. The government also reset the tax-free income limit at Tk 180,000 for women taxpayers and those aged over 70, the chief adviser's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim said after a cabinet meeting. The cabinet approved the budget for fiscal 2008-09. In the budget announced on June 9, finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam proposed to raise the tax-free income limit only for women and the 70-plus persons by Tk 15,000. bdnews24.c
